markupReviewDTO.markupBasedOnSellContractLanguage1: Except as otherwise set forth in Section 6 of the Agreement the price for the Products will be Cost on the date of the order plus the applicable category mark-up (the �Mark-Up�); or, in the case of a percentage Mark-Up, the price is Cost divided by the difference between one (1.0) and the Mark-Up (for example, 0.9 would be used for a 10% mark-up). If a Location requires a Product to be sold in less than full case quantities and such Product can be split into individual units, the split case fee referenced in Section 4 below will be included in the sell price.
markupReviewDTO.markupTypeDefinitionSellUnitLanguage: The sell price for a Catch Weight Product subject to a dollar Mark-Up by "Sell Unit" identified in Section 4 of this Exhibit ("Sell Unit Fee") is Cost per pound based on the average case weight in preceding periods as reasonably determined by GFS plus the Sell Unit Fee. For example, the sell price for a pound of Product with a $3.00 Cost per pound and a $2.00 Sell Unit Fee would be $5.00 per pound.
markupReviewDTO.markupTypeDefinitionPerCaseLanguage: The sell price for a Catch Weight Product subject to a dollar Mark-Up "Per Case" identified in Section 4 of this Exhibit ("Per Case Fee") is the Cost per pound plus the Per Case Fee, converted to a cents per pound fee based upon the average case weight of the Catch Weight Product. The average case weight shall be based on the average of case weights for the Catch Weight Product in preceding periods as reasonably determined by GFS. For example, the sell price for a pound of Product with a $3.00 Cost per pound and a $2.00 Per Case Fee with an average case weight of 20 pounds would be $3.10 per pound ($2.00 / 20 = $0.10 + $3.00 = $3.10).
markupReviewDTO.markupTypeDefinitionPerWeightLanguage: For each "Per Weight" Mark-Up identified in Section 4 of this Exhibit, the Mark-Up shall apply to each one pound (or part of one pound) of Product according to the actual Cost per pound; or, if not purchased by GFS at a Cost per pound, the Cost converted to a Cost per pound based on the average Case weight in preceding periods as reasonably determined by GFS.
markupReviewDTO.markupBasedOnSellContractLanguage2: If Customer has negotiated a specific allowance with a vendor on one or more Products, then such allowance will be deducted from the sell price of the Product, after the Mark-Up has been applied.

splitCaseReviewDTO.feeTypeContractLanguage: The sell price of a Case Unit will be the full Case sell price divided by the number of Case Units in the Case plus any applicable split case fee listed in Section 4 of this Exhibit.
